        "body": "## Summary\n\n- make the live VNC surface use the full Mac window without rounded inset borders\n- compact the toolbar, desktop switcher, and status bar\n- negotiate RFB ExtendedDesktopSize updates as the viewer changes size, with request coalescing, capability gating, and rejection-safe fallback\n- use an available stable local signing identity so Keychain authorization survives dev rebuilds\n\n## Testing\n\n- `swift test --package-path macos/CrabfleetMac` (77 tests)\n- `swift test --package-path macos/CrabfleetMac/Vendor/RoyalVNCKit` (26 tests)\n- `pnpm check`\n- `pnpm macos:bundle`\n- `codesign --verify --deep --strict macos/CrabfleetMac/.build/Crabfleet.app`\n- live macOS RoyalVNCKit → Ubuntu 24.04 TigerVNC integration: `connected=true resize_supported=true requested=true framebuffer=1280x720`\n- server confirmation after the same request: `Screen 0: minimum 32 x 32, current 1280 x 720, maximum 32768 x 32768`\n\nStructured local autoreview was attempted but blocked by host data-export policy; manual review completed instead.\n\n## Review follow-up\n\n- corrected the reviewed SetDesktopSize header from 10 bytes to the protocol-defined 8 bytes\n- retained the changelog entry because workspace policy requires maintainer/AI changelog coverage for user-facing fixes\n",
